Encode Sans Condensed Thin Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-Thin.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansCondensed-Thin', Everything looks good.

Encode Sans Condensed Thin Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Condensed Thin'.

Encode Sans Condensed ExLight Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansCondensed-ExtraLight', Everything looks good.

Encode Sans Condensed Light Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Condensed Light'.

Encode Sans Condensed Medium Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Condensed Medium'.

Pass

Encode Sans Condensed SemiBold Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-SemiBold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansCondensed-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Encode Sans Condensed SemiBold Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansCondensed-SemiBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Encode Sans Condensed SemiBold Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Condensed SemiBold'.

Pass

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Condensed ExtraBold'.

Pass

Encode Sans Condensed Black Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-Black.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansCondensed-Black', Everything looks good.

Pass

Encode Sans Condensed Black Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'EncodeSansCondensed-Black', Everything looks good.

Pass

Encode Sans Condensed Black Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Encode Sans Condensed' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Encode Sans Condensed Black'.

underlinePosition should be a negative and underlineThickness not 0 or negative.

underlinePosition is '-75'.
underlineThicknes is '50'.

Kerning (kern Table and GPOS Kerning)

Kerning (kern Table and GPOS Kerning)

Pass

Encode Sans Condensed Thin Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-Thin.ttf)

GPOS

kern

Simple check if kern feature in GPOS table.

The font has GPOS kerning.

Info

Encode Sans Condensed Thin Regular (EncodeSansCondensed-Thin.ttf)

kern

-/-

Check if 'kern' table in font.

Font has no 'kern' table. Please verify if font requires kern table or if only GPOS kerning should be in font.

Info

kern/GPOS

Font has GPOS kerning and no 'kern' table.
Verify with the spec or PM what is required.

OS/2 and head

sTypeAsc/Desc and unitsPerEm

The result of sTypoAscender – sTypoDescender should match or exceed the unitsPerEm value.

The result of sTypoAscender – sTypoDescender (2500) match or exceed the unitsPerEm value (2000).
